external_knowledge:
- "enchantments floating in the ether" refers to spells in the database;
- "invoked by a minimum of six unique wizards" means the spell must have been cast by more than five distinct users;
- "identities" refers to the spell's unique identifier and its name;
- "pace at which they dance into existence" metaphorically refers to the average time at which the spells were cast;
- "frequency of their summonings" refers to how many times the spell has been used.

- 'ignite like wildfire' metaphorically refers to spells belonging to the 'Fire' school;
- 'cast as swiftly as a flash' is a metaphor for spells that have an 'Instant' casting time;
- 'resting period' refers to the cooldown time of spells.

sql:
SELECT difficulty_id, COUNT(spell_id) AS spell_count
FROM spells
GROUP BY difficulty_id;

SELECT name, cooldown
FROM spells
ORDER BY cooldown DESC;

SELECT name
FROM spells
WHERE spell_id = 1;

SELECT name
FROM spells
WHERE mana_cost = (SELECT MIN(mana_cost) FROM spells);

SELECT spell_id, usage_count
FROM spell_analytics
ORDER BY usage_count DESC;

SELECT name
FROM spells
WHERE is_enabled = 1;

